; Card graphics. Each "<Name>CardGfx": 3 GBC palettes (rgb) + a 48-entry
; attribute map (db; high 2 bits = each tile's palette, low 6 = a tile index
; for the alternate LoadCardGfxRemapped renderer), then INCBIN of the 48
; portrait tiles (built from gfx/cards/<name>.png, 4-shade grayscale, column-
; major). A "<Name>CardGfxExtra" + INCBIN follows for cards whose printer
; rendering pulls in extra tiles past the portrait; `ds` runs are inter-card
; alignment padding. gfx/cards/misc/*.bin are the still-unlabeled gfx that
; share these banks ahead of CardGraphics. Generated by
; tools/extract_card_gfx.py.

